==Personal life & Death ==
During the glory period he is a celebrity like a superstar. He married a popular actress in that era Prim Prapaporn. The couple have one son, he named his son Kriangsak "King" Mansri, just like the name of the [[Prime Minister of Thailand|prime minister]] at the time Gen. [[Kriangsak Chamanan]].

The end of boxing, he was injured, especially the right eye. When he retired his right eye is blind. His wife divorced him. And his savings of up to 10 million [[Thai baht|baht]] was exhausted. Ever since his life is hard living. He has a monthly courtesy from WBC and other authorities in Thailand. But it was not enough for the cost.<ref name="หน้า">หน้า 37-41, "หมัดซ้ายสีชมพู" แสนศักดิ์ เมืองสุรินทร์ แชมป์โลกชาวไทยคนที่ห้า รุ่นซูเปอร์ไลท์เวท WBC. "22 แชมป์โลกชาวไทย" นิตยสารคนเด็ด (เฉพาะกิจพิเศษ) โดย "ชายพจน์": ตุลาคม 38 {{th icon}}</ref>

Saensak was admitted to Rajvithi Hospital on April 12, 2009 for liver failure and intestinal blockage. Surgery failed to improve his condition, which was complicated by Saensak being afflicted by various ailments. On April 16, Saensak died while under observation in an [[intensive care unit]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/sports/15149/thai-legend-saensak-dies-at-58|title=Thai legend Saensak dies at 58|last=Thangarajah|first=Edward|date=2009-04-17|work=[[Bangkok Post]]|accessdate=2009-04-18}}</ref>

